        @Nullable
 @Contract(pure=true)
@Nullable GuiElement<?> getChild(int column,
                                                                 int row)
        Gets the element at the specified column-row pair. Returns null if there isn't an element at the specified position. Indexing starts at 0.
        Parameters:
        column - the column the element is contained in
        row - the row the element is contained in
        Returns:
        the matching element or null, if none were found

@NotNull GridGuiContainer setGridSize(int columns,

      • makeChild

        @NotNull
<E extends GuiElement<E>> E makeChild(@NotNull
                                               E element,
                                               int column,
                                               int row)
        Makes the specified element a direct child of this container. If the element is already a child it is moved to the new position if necessary. The element is inserted into the specified column-row pair. An exception is thrown if that position already contains an element. Indexing starts at 0.
        Type Parameters:
        E - the type of the element
        Parameters:
        element - the element to add as as child
        column - the column the element should be inserted into
        row - the row the element should be inserted into
        Returns:
        the new child (for chaining)
